This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on generating synthetic images for downstream tasks. Additionally, the use of a graphics engine and neural network to modify scene graphs suggests a strong emphasis on visual data. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.AI) as it uses a generative model and neural network to synthesize data. The optimization of a meta-objective for downstream task performance suggests a focus on reinforcement learning (cs.LG) or optimization (cs.GT). Finally, the use of probabilistic scene grammars suggests a potential connection to computer graphics (cs.GR).
